1
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:09,200
Wait.

2
00:00:17,520 --> 00:00:18,320
Honey.

3
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:22,090
Your tie is crooked.

4
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:28,000
What would I do without you?

5
00:00:30,120 --> 00:00:31,120
By the way, honey,

6
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:33,280
I want to discuss something with you.

7
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:34,080
Go ahead.

8
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:36,800
Xixi is getting older,

9
00:00:37,680 --> 00:00:39,080
so I want to find a job.

10
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:46,080
That's good. You shouldn't stay home all the time.

11
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:47,520
I don't want you

12
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:49,720
to be like those full-time housewives,

13
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,480
revolving around the kid all day

14
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:53,210
and losing touch with society.

15
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:54,200
But...

16
00:00:56,440 --> 00:00:57,080
But what?

17
00:00:58,040 --> 00:00:59,680
You haven't worked in years

18
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:01,240
and lack social experience.

19
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:02,700
What if someone scams you?

20
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:06,220
How about this?

21
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:08,210
Come to my company to practice.

22
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:09,640
I'll make you the legal representative.

23
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:11,280
How about I work for you?

24
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:14,600
Honey,

25
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,280
you're so good to me.

26
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:22,940
But I don't know anything.

27
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:26,680
I'm afraid people at the company will laugh at me.

28
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:31,800
Let me think about it.

29
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:33,120
Okay.

30
00:01:33,479 --> 00:01:34,280
Go to work.

31
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:35,160
Don't be late.

32
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:38,520
By the way.

33
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:41,920
There's a team building event tonight.

34
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:43,000
I'll be back late.

35
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:44,960
Don't wait up for dinner.

36
00:01:45,039 --> 00:01:45,840
Got it.

37
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:46,920
Go on.

38
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,539
Be careful on your way.

39
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:16,000
He didn't notice anything.

40
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,000
Received.

41
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:00,360
Is this green?

42
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,640
Yes.

43
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,440
Who are you going to draw this time?

44
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:07,640
Are you drawing Elsa?

45
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:10,320
I'll draw the same one as before.

46
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:11,600
The same one?

47
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:12,520
Yeah.

48
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:17,860
What are you doing?

49
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:21,840
Are you taking advantage of my son's absence

50
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,079
to hide some man here?

51
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:37,460
Why are you fiddling with these lousy paintings again?

52
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:39,200
Put that down.

53
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,720
What are you doing?

54
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:44,960
Put it down.

55
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,040
Mom, there's a company

56
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,450
that offered me a high-paying job.

57
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:58,640
These are the materials I prepared.

58
00:03:58,640 --> 00:04:00,160
I was just about to head out.

59
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:00,960
High-paying?

60
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:02,680
You?

61
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:05,000
Does it pay more than my son?

62
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,860
In the years you've been married,

63
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:09,160
you've relied on my son for everything.

64
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:11,960
If it were up to you, you'd be begging on the street.

65
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:14,560
Besides, if you go to work,

66
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:16,339
who will take care of Xixi?

67
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:19,959
You're right.

68
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:24,040
Chen Jian has been busy taking care of the family these years.

69
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,250
He works so hard.

70
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,920
My heart aches for him.

71
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:29,320
So,

72
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:31,450
I was just thinking about finding a job

73
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:32,780
to relieve his stress.

74
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:37,000
And the company

75
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:40,840
offered me an annual salary of one million.

76
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,080
One million?

77
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:46,440
Why don't you go for it?

78
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:49,720
I'm still hesitating.

79
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:53,800
What is there to hesitate about?

80
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:56,600
If I go to work,

81
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,530
what about Xixi?

82
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,640
I'm here, aren't I?

83
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,480
My own precious granddaughter,

84
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:03,920
can't I take care of her?

85
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,320
Come here, Xixi.

86
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:07,680
Come to Grandma.

87
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:09,240
Xixi,

88
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,720
come to Grandma.

89
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:13,040
Hurry, Xixi.

90
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,680
Come to Grandma.

91
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:19,720
Let Mommy go to work.

92
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,680
Why are you still standing there?

93
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,040
Hurry up and go.

94
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:26,320
Grandma.

95
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,880
Mom, thanks for your trouble.

96
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:31,440
Chen Jian and I

97
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:35,200
will take care of you forever.

98
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:36,840
Go on now.

99
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:38,400
Xixi.

100
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:39,720
Play with Grandma at home.

101
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:40,520
Mommy is going to work.

102
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:40,920
Okay.

103
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,600
Okay?

104
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:45,080
The second little ghost looks nice.

105
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:49,720
Xixi, Mommy is going to work.

106
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:52,000
Come here. Tell Grandma.

107
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,720
What is this drawing?

108
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:20,920
Thank you.

109
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:31,920
Hello, sir.

110
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:33,409
How is it?

111
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:35,720
Lights ready.

112
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:37,159
Big screen ready.

113
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,800
Control panel ready.

114
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,200
Everything is ready.

115
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:42,240
Okay.

116
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:43,040
Let's go.

117
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:05,080
Distinguished guests, colleagues,

118
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:06,680
good evening.

119
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,320
Good evening!

120
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,640
For our livestreaming company

121
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:12,480
to achieve the success we have today,

122
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,010
we have one person to thank.

123
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:15,640
No.

124
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,080
To be exact, she isn't a person.

125
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,840
She is a

126
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:21,360
cute kitty.

127
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:24,980
She conquered half the livestreaming world for us.

128
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:25,840
Now,

129
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:28,840
please welcome her to the stage.

130
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,680
Strawberry Meow!

131
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:40,120
Grass's Strawberry Meow Meow.

132
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:43,960
Strawberry-Loving Kitten.

133
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:48,320
No Strawberry Meow Meow.

134
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:54,000
Thank you all for your support tonight.

135
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,640
Moving forward,

136
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,680
I hope we can keep working hard together

137
00:07:57,680 --> 00:08:01,600
to build up Mr. Chen's live streaming business.

138
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:02,400
Okay?

139
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,680
Okay!

140
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:06,080
Come on, everyone, raise your glasses.

141
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:08,320
Let's get this party started.

142
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:19,000
Spread out, everyone.

143
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:21,040
Enjoy the night.

144
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:40,880
Great.

145
00:08:58,320 --> 00:09:00,720
Is this a new streamer our company signed?

146
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,700
Why haven't I seen her before?

147
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,520
Why is she here?

148
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:40,840
Can you dance?

149
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:42,450
I don't know how.

150
00:10:59,000 --> 00:10:59,920
Are you ready?

151
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:08,400
What are you doing here?

152
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:09,330
Am I not welcome?

153
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:11,000
Of course you are. Welcome.

154
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,860
Honey, you look beautiful today.

155
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:18,840
Isn't that Mrs. Chen?

156
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,480
Mr. Chen can dance, too?

157
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,160
Mr. Chen, show us!

158
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:24,400
Show us! Music!

159
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:27,480
Show us!

160
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:30,200
Show us!

161
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:32,160
Show us!
